AI5Z is a real-time web application that aggregates live Solana token market data from Birdeye, PumpPortal, and PumpFunChat WebSocket streams and triggers multi-AI conversations orchestrated through OpenRouter API. The system uses an event queue architecture where a director AI selects speakers from five models (GPT-4o-mini, Grok-4-fast, Claude-3.5-Sonnet, Deepseek, Gemini) based on market events, trade activities, and user chat messages, generating contextual responses with ElevenLabs text-to-speech synthesis. Built with Node.js/Express backend and Socket.IO for bidirectional real-time communication, displaying aggregated market data, trades, and AI dialogues in a terminal-style interface.
